							<p>Explore how knowledge of anatomy is crucial in sports medicine, injury prevention, and rehabilitation. Discuss pathologies in human anatomy and congenital anomalies, shedding light on their clinical significance. Highlight recent advancements in brain research, emphasizing the exploration of the brain's structure and function through cutting-edge techniques like neuroimaging and connectomics. Engage in discussions about the application of engineering materials and biomechanical principles to comprehend and improve biological structures and functions. Delve into the latest breakthroughs in imaging technologies though AI-based digital pathology, and evaluate MRI, CT, and microscopy, elucidating to their applications in anatomical and cell biology research.</p>
